---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';

const team = [
  { title: 'A doctor, always watching', text: 'A physician is on duty every hour we are open — not on call, not down the hall, but here, watching your treatment and ready to act the moment anything changes.' },
  { title: 'Dietitians who speak Filipino food', text: 'A kidney diet you can actually live with, built around sinigang and rice and the food on your own table — not a printout of things you will never eat.' },
  { title: 'Social workers in your corner', text: 'PhilHealth, the paperwork, the money worries — the parts of dialysis nobody warns you about. Our social workers carry them with you, so you can carry less.' },
  { title: 'Diagnostics without the runaround', text: 'We coordinate your bloodwork and labs with trusted, well-known partner laboratories. Reliable results, on time, without you chasing them across the city.' },
];
---
<BaseLayout title="Services" description="Hemodialysis matched to you, a full team around your chair, and the invisible safety work — innovator medicines, maker-calibrated machines, dual-pass RO water — that keeps you safe at St. John Biocare." image="/images/og/og-services.jpg">
  <PageHero
    image="/images/photos/dsc_0038.webp"
    alt="A St. John Biocare dialysis treatment area with monitoring equipment"
    eyebrow="Services"
    title="Everything your dialysis care needs."
    subtitle="The machines, the medicines, the water, the people — every detail that keeps you safe, in the hands of a team that has done this for fifteen years."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container stack" style="max-width:760px">
      <p class="lead">Kidney failure asks something enormous of you: to hand your life to strangers, three
      times a week, for years. We never forget that. So we built this place around a single promise — that
      you can walk in, sit down, and simply be cared for, while we quietly carry the thousand details you
      should never have to think about.</p>
      <p>Here is what your care includes — and, just as important, the standards behind it that you will
      never see from your chair. In a field where it has become all too easy to quietly do less, we have
      staked our name on doing more.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--mist">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <p class="eyebrow">The treatment</p>
      <h2>There is no standard patient. So we don't run standard sessions.</h2>
      <p>Hemodialysis is the heart of what we do — modern machines, close monitoring, strict infection
      control, and early-morning schedules built for people who still have work to get to and families to
      go home to. But two people can carry the same diagnosis and need very different treatment. Yours
      should fit <em>you</em>.</p>
      <p>That is why we offer the full range, and choose it with you: <strong>low-flux</strong> and
      <strong>high-flux hemodialysis</strong>, <strong>hemodiafiltration (HDF)</strong> at select branches
      when you need more thorough clearance, <strong>SLED</strong> — a gentler, slower session — for the
      days your body is fragile, and <strong>isolated ultrafiltration (UF)</strong> when the problem is
      excess fluid, not toxins. Your prescription is a medical decision, revisited as you change. Never a
      default left on the machine.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <p class="eyebrow">The team around your chair</p>
      <h2>A machine cleans your blood. People keep you well.</h2>
      <p>The best equipment in the world is only as good as the people watching over it. So your care here
      is wrapped in a whole team — and we take the time to explain everything in plain language, because a
      patient who understands what is happening is a patient who does better. When you know your treatment,
      you become part of it.</p>

      <div class="grid grid--2" style="margin-top:22px">
        {team.map((m) => (
          <div class="card">
            <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">{m.title}</h3>
            <p style="margin:0">{m.text}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--mist">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <p class="eyebrow">Quality &amp; safety</p>
      <h2>The safety you can't see is the safety that matters most.</h2>
      <p>Anyone can put a chair and a machine in a room. What actually keeps you safe happens where you
      never look — in the medicines, the water, the calibration, the cleaning. These are the corners that
      can be cut where no patient would ever notice. We built our name on refusing to cut them — not
      because someone is watching, but because excellence is the whole reason we exist.</p>

      <div class="grid grid--2" style="margin-top:22px">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Innovator medicines — never the substitute</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">The medicines in your line are <strong>innovator (original-brand)
          products</strong> — the original manufacturers' own erythropoietin, intravenous iron and
          <strong>Halal-certified heparin</strong>, held to the same standard as every material and
          chemical we use. When margins come first, medicine is the first thing to quietly change. Not
          here — the cheaper copy may share a name, but your body knows the difference.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Trusted machines, tuned by their makers</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">Every center runs hemodialysis machines from <strong>well-known, established
          brands — locally and internationally</strong>, and we let no one but the <strong>original
          manufacturers</strong> calibrate them, on a regular schedule. The equipment caring for you
          performs exactly as it was built to.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Water purified twice, before it ever reaches you</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">The water in dialysis meets your bloodstream — so it must be
          extraordinarily pure. Every center treats its water through a <strong>dual-pass reverse-osmosis
          (RO)</strong> system, cleansing it twice over before a single drop reaches a machine. That is a
          standard we hold across the entire network.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">Infection control, by protocol not by luck</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">Careful, protocol-driven dialyzer reprocessing and formal infection-control
          practices govern every session. It is disciplined, unglamorous, repetitive work — and it is
          exactly the work that keeps you safe, session after session.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.15rem">On the day we close, we work hardest</h3>
          <p style="margin:0">We shut our doors to patients on <strong>Sundays</strong> — and that is when
          the deepest work begins: <strong>wall-to-wall clinic disinfection</strong> and full servicing of
          the <strong>water treatment system</strong>, from disinfection and calibration to resetting and
          maintenance. You come back Monday to a center cleaned and checked from top to bottom.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--forest">
    <div class="container center" style="max-width:720px">
      <p class="eyebrow">Come see for yourself</p>
      <h2>This is what it means to be cared for here.</h2>
      <p style="color:#e5f3e9;font-size:1.15rem">Nothing left to chance. Nothing you have to chase. Just
      good, careful dialysis — and people who treat your safety as their own. Visit a center, meet the
      team, and let us show you the difference in person.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:22px"><a href="/new-patients#request" class="btn btn--light">Request an appointment</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--sand" style="padding-block:44px">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:920px">
      <figure style="margin:0">
        <picture>
          <source srcset="/images/og/og-services.webp" type="image/webp" />
          <img src="/images/og/og-services.jpg" width="1200" height="630" loading="lazy"
               alt="St. John Biocare services at a glance: hemodialysis, physicians on duty, renal dietitians, and social workers."
               style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:14px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)" />
        </picture>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
